narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments:
deepened understanding of English and English grammar;
foundation in Latin vocabulary, grammar, and syntax;

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: deeply thorough, included explanations of Latin grammar from a linguistic/analytical perspective
Weaknesses: could have benefitted from more accountability on vocab words. 

The amount of vocabulary introduced every day felt overwhelming to keep track of, so having frequent quizzes on vocabulary would have been helpful practice.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, after college you will never have another opportunity to spend a whole summer learning, practicing, and reading Latin.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: I will use the deepened understanding of English to improve my essay writing. Having a foundation of Latin will also be useful for reading the Vulgate and other Catholic liturgy and literature.
